00:59.693 --> 01:03.164
Megan, welcome to
Creative Partners.

01:10.538 --> 01:12.540
If you had to ask,
does it matter?

01:12.573 --> 01:14.142
Sure, it does.

01:15.609 --> 01:20.581
'Cause if it's fake, it's fake.

01:21.549 --> 01:23.884
Smart, principled, no bullshit.

01:23.917 --> 01:25.453
Is that the New Yorker in you,

01:25.486 --> 01:27.588
or is that the narrative
you crafted at IHM?

01:28.922 --> 01:30.524
I did the weekend intensive.

01:30.558 --> 01:32.193
We all did.

01:32.226 --> 01:34.395
Terence is an amazing talent,
isn't he?

01:34.428 --> 01:36.430
Yeah. Yeah, he is.

01:36.464 --> 01:38.432
Speaking of no bullshit,

01:38.466 --> 01:42.336
has anyone here seen
any of my work.

01:42.370 --> 01:44.314
You think we just rolled out
the red carpet for you

01:44.338 --> 01:46.207
because you're Kyle's fiancÃ©e?

01:46.240 --> 01:48.242
Well, I know you did, but...

01:48.276 --> 01:50.144
I asked about my work.

01:50.178 --> 01:52.880
What there is of it, yeah.
We have seen it.

01:52.913 --> 01:55.216
You've made the best
of small opportunities,

01:55.249 --> 01:57.318
but now your time has come.

01:57.351 --> 01:59.253
We all believe that
"Technicolor Highway"

01:59.287 --> 02:00.354
is gonna make you a star.

02:00.388 --> 02:01.922
Separate and apart from Kyle.

02:03.657 --> 02:05.493
We're gonna make you an icon.

02:05.526 --> 02:08.461
No, I don't need
to be an icon, I...

02:08.496 --> 02:10.931
Look, I just wanna get
my hands on great projects

02:10.964 --> 02:13.367
that I can lose myself in.

02:13.401 --> 02:15.503
Megan, we're the biggest
agency in the world.

02:15.536 --> 02:18.372
Getting your hands on great
projects will not be a problem.

02:18.406 --> 02:20.908
Getting you cast
is something else.

02:20.941 --> 02:22.410
Yeah, that's my job.

02:22.443 --> 02:24.345
It's true.
Thank God you're talented.

02:26.214 --> 02:28.749
But listen,
when you're the face of Prada,

02:28.782 --> 02:31.385
and Bulgari, and
the charity of your choosing...

02:31.419 --> 02:34.655
When you are a goodwill
ambassador to the world,

02:34.688 --> 02:37.325
I promise you, your job
gets a lot easier.

02:37.358 --> 02:39.927
If you don't like the word
"icon" then don't use it.

02:39.960 --> 02:41.695
Think of it as brand.

02:41.729 --> 02:45.233
Megan Morrison...
Like, Marilyn Monroe.

02:45.266 --> 02:47.668
- She died at 36.
- She had the wrong agent.

02:47.701 --> 02:50.371
It's not just about
being sought after.

02:50.404 --> 02:52.473
Your brand,
if we craft it correctly,

02:52.506 --> 02:53.674
gives you control.

02:53.707 --> 02:55.409
And longevity.

02:55.443 --> 02:57.445
So the real Megan can focus
on what she wants,

02:57.478 --> 03:00.748
what really matters.

03:11.525 --> 03:15.263
Dude! Why would you fire
yourself from your own movie?

03:15.296 --> 03:16.573
Right? It's... it's... I'm sorry.

03:16.597 --> 03:18.766
It just... it seems unwise
on so many levels.

03:18.799 --> 03:19.800
No, I get it.

03:19.833 --> 03:21.569
You know, I just...

03:21.602 --> 03:23.447
I thought it was more important
to focus on directing.

03:23.471 --> 03:25.439
And...
And let Megan carry the film.

03:25.473 --> 03:26.783
And you... you honestly
think she can do that?

03:26.807 --> 03:28.342
Put people in the seats?

03:28.376 --> 03:29.553
Megan's gonna
blow everybody away.

03:29.577 --> 03:31.279
Wow.

03:31.312 --> 03:33.423
I wish... I wish everybody
could've seen the man's face

03:33.447 --> 03:34.815
when he said that.

03:34.848 --> 03:36.393
II'm so inspired...
I feel like I can just run

03:36.417 --> 03:37.657
through a brick wall right now.

03:37.685 --> 03:38.795
The power of truth,
ladies and gentlemen.

03:38.819 --> 03:40.588
Okay, so tell me this.

03:40.621 --> 03:43.391
Does Megan get a say
in who takes your place?

03:43.424 --> 03:44.768
You know, we are... we're
gonna find the perfect person.

03:44.792 --> 03:46.594
I promise.

03:46.627 --> 03:48.827
All right, well, I happen
to be available, by the way.

03:49.730 --> 03:53.000
I'd love to meet this perfect
person who's replacing you.

03:53.033 --> 03:54.802
You don't like Howie
for the part?

03:54.835 --> 03:56.446
You know, that would be funny
if you weren't saying no

03:56.470 --> 03:58.472
to every actor that I suggest.

03:58.506 --> 04:00.550
They don't wanna audition,
they're not doing the movie.

04:00.574 --> 04:01.742
Period.

04:07.381 --> 04:08.782
So did you get
the big standing O?

04:08.816 --> 04:11.619
I did, and then
they promised me the world.

04:11.652 --> 04:13.621
Well, they pretty much
represent the world.

04:13.654 --> 04:14.622
What do you think?

04:14.655 --> 04:16.724
It's very compelling.

04:16.757 --> 04:17.757
A little disgusting.

04:17.791 --> 04:19.493
It's a lot to process.

04:19.527 --> 04:21.629
Okay, well, why don't
we go to the beach?

04:21.661 --> 04:23.397
I'll clear my afternoon.

04:23.431 --> 04:24.671
No, you don't have to do that.

04:24.698 --> 04:26.434
I'm on the other side of town.

04:26.467 --> 04:28.336
And I have a bunch
of errands to run.

04:28.369 --> 04:29.579
We could talk about it tonight.

04:29.603 --> 04:32.340
Okay, whatever you want.

04:33.807 --> 04:35.843
Is everything okay with you two?

04:35.876 --> 04:37.645
Of course.
Little stuff... no big deal.

04:39.513 --> 04:41.525
Because it would be awfully
hard to choose a love interest

04:41.549 --> 04:44.051
for her if you
two weren't... solid.

04:44.084 --> 04:45.786
Well, we're solid enough.

04:45.819 --> 04:47.831
Just literally trying
to find the right actor, DeAnn.

04:47.855 --> 04:49.899
And there isn't a part
of you that's a little worried

04:49.923 --> 04:52.426
about history repeating itself?

04:52.460 --> 04:54.061
No.

04:54.094 --> 04:57.365
And do me a favor...
Let's keep history in the past,

04:57.398 --> 04:58.899
where it belongs.

05:12.546 --> 05:14.682
That's one way
to release stress, I guess.

05:14.715 --> 05:17.551
Babe, that's not what that was.

05:17.585 --> 05:18.786
Not completely.

05:21.789 --> 05:23.657
How do you know these things?

05:23.691 --> 05:25.759
We spend one weekend
a year together.

05:25.793 --> 05:29.430
That's not nothing.

05:29.463 --> 05:31.665
So...

05:31.699 --> 05:32.700
Tell me.

05:32.733 --> 05:35.836
This movie.

05:35.869 --> 05:38.806
It's like on existential crisis
after another,

05:38.839 --> 05:40.674
and it...

05:40.708 --> 05:43.444
It's just...
It's so personal for Kyle.

05:43.477 --> 05:45.846
It's like he can't
see things rationally.

05:45.879 --> 05:47.156
Well, like what kind of things?

05:47.180 --> 05:49.650
Well...

05:49.683 --> 05:51.485
No.

05:51.519 --> 05:54.822
You are leaving soon, and I am
not gonna lie in bed with you

05:54.855 --> 05:57.691
bitching about Kyle,
because I do that with Terence.

05:57.725 --> 06:00.561
Lucky him.

06:01.795 --> 06:03.864
Babe, these are our lives.

06:03.897 --> 06:05.866
I would've loved to have
had you in my bed

06:05.899 --> 06:07.868
when Wes was in rehab.

06:07.901 --> 06:10.671
So we could've talked about
my failings as a mother.

06:10.704 --> 06:12.172
Stop.

06:12.205 --> 06:15.743
You know you're the only reason
he's still alive.

06:15.776 --> 06:18.479
He's alive.

06:18.512 --> 06:20.781
I don't know, I just worry.

06:20.814 --> 06:23.484
No, we're not doing this.

06:23.517 --> 06:24.852
Worry.

06:24.885 --> 06:25.886
Why are you laughing?

06:25.919 --> 06:27.521
Because you're right.

06:27.555 --> 06:28.865
I should save this shit
for book club.

06:28.889 --> 06:30.691
Yeah, book club.

06:30.724 --> 06:33.861
Yeah, that's what I need.

06:33.894 --> 06:38.632
I wanna talk about you.

06:38.666 --> 06:42.603
I wanna know what you
dreamt about last night.

06:42.636 --> 06:44.938
I wanna cook you dinner.

06:48.041 --> 06:51.645
See, this is the bad part
about you staying longer.

06:51.679 --> 06:53.781
It's the worst kind of tease.

06:53.814 --> 06:56.617
Well, you know, technically,

06:56.650 --> 06:58.919
I don't have to be on site
until the summer.

06:58.952 --> 07:01.622
I mean, the vineyard has plenty
of business in LA,

07:01.655 --> 07:03.724
and Wes is close by.

07:03.757 --> 07:05.793
You wanna stay until summer?

07:05.826 --> 07:08.462
Yeah.

07:10.631 --> 07:12.933
It's been a tough year.
I... I don't know.

07:12.966 --> 07:15.969
I wanna spend more time
with the people that I love.

07:16.003 --> 07:18.706
More than just one weekend.

07:20.741 --> 07:23.844
Why do you look
so terrified at that?

07:23.877 --> 07:25.646
- No, I'm not... it's not...
- Yeah, you do.

07:25.679 --> 07:28.916
No, no, it's not that.
It's just that...

07:31.051 --> 07:34.688
Look, when you leave...

07:34.722 --> 07:36.690
Terence and I get
there eventually,

07:36.724 --> 07:39.226
but it's a rough transition.

07:39.259 --> 07:43.664
If you stay, we're talking
about a fullblown affair.

07:43.697 --> 07:45.833
Yeah.

07:45.866 --> 07:48.001
That's what it would be.

07:50.571 --> 07:52.606
Mace, my marriage
might be dysfunctional,

07:52.640 --> 07:55.242
but I can't afford
to ruin it... not now.

07:55.275 --> 07:58.579
I'm not asking you to.

07:58.612 --> 08:02.282
Babe, I just don't wanna
leave you right now.

08:06.887 --> 08:09.289
So let's not be afraid
to admit it.

08:09.322 --> 08:11.091
Let's say it together...
I'm gonna be great.

08:11.124 --> 08:12.893
I'm gonna be great.

08:12.926 --> 08:14.695
- I'm gonna be great.
- I'm gonna be great.

08:14.728 --> 08:15.896
Come on, guys, lets...

08:15.929 --> 08:17.931
So are you watching the speech

08:17.965 --> 08:19.800
or are you just
counting the views?

08:19.833 --> 08:21.869
I'm gonna be great!

08:21.902 --> 08:23.737
You know, he's always had that.

08:23.771 --> 08:26.874
That magnetic thing that
people are attracted to.

08:26.907 --> 08:28.609
I saw it the day I met him.

08:28.642 --> 08:31.645
He was nobody, he had nothing,
but he had that.

08:31.679 --> 08:35.549
And you're surprised
by the response you're getting?

08:35.582 --> 08:37.326
When it gets to 15 million
call Scholastic.

08:37.350 --> 08:39.852
Or maybe I will.

08:39.886 --> 08:42.956
Um... I'm... I'm all packed up
and ready to go,

08:42.990 --> 08:45.593
I just wanted to say thank you.

08:47.060 --> 08:49.797
James starts training
at the Facility tomorrow.

08:49.830 --> 08:52.099
Yeah, can't wait.

08:54.367 --> 08:56.637
Um... end of next month.

08:57.705 --> 08:59.773
Wow, okay.

08:59.807 --> 09:02.576
Well, safe travels.

09:02.610 --> 09:05.345
Good luck.

09:05.378 --> 09:07.915
You okay?

09:09.950 --> 09:11.719
You seem a little disappointed.

09:11.752 --> 09:12.953
What?

09:12.986 --> 09:14.788
No, no, no, no... just...

09:14.822 --> 09:19.793
Busy with some things.

09:47.387 --> 09:50.357
Hi. Come in.

10:00.801 --> 10:04.004
No paparazzi, and no IHM tail.

10:04.037 --> 10:05.839
You must be a good driver.

10:05.873 --> 10:08.175
Well, I learned
from cabbies in New York City,

10:08.208 --> 10:10.010
so it's not necessarily
good, but...

10:12.813 --> 10:15.783
It's Momordica charantia.
It purifies the blood.

10:15.816 --> 10:17.184
Thank you.

10:17.217 --> 10:19.019
And thank you again
for having me over.

10:19.052 --> 10:20.954
This is really lovely.

10:23.957 --> 10:25.225
Um...

10:25.258 --> 10:27.661
I'm really sorry about the way

10:27.695 --> 10:29.997
I approached you
the other night.

10:30.030 --> 10:33.133
I have to be careful
about who I interact with.

10:33.166 --> 10:36.904
The world is extremely toxic.

10:39.006 --> 10:41.709
But that can't be you.

10:41.742 --> 10:43.944
Kyle wouldn't love you
if it was.

10:53.153 --> 10:56.957
There are so many things
I wanna ask you, um...

10:57.958 --> 11:00.160
Can we start with Terence?

11:00.193 --> 11:04.164
He's done things that should've
destroyed me and Kyle,

11:04.197 --> 11:07.768
and it makes me wonder
if he did something

11:07.801 --> 11:10.771
to make you leave.

11:10.804 --> 11:13.440
They poisoned my food and water.

11:13.473 --> 11:15.743
By who?

11:15.776 --> 11:18.178
By IHM people?
They'd break into my trailer.

11:18.211 --> 11:20.714
Never the same person...
Not once.

11:20.748 --> 11:23.216
I mean, there were
always new people.

11:23.250 --> 11:24.918
That isn't normal.

11:24.952 --> 11:26.820
Did you tell Kyle about this,
or anyone?

11:26.854 --> 11:28.021
Kyle wasn't there.

11:28.055 --> 11:31.058
I mean, I had to fire everybody.

11:31.091 --> 11:33.226
I still have problems eating.

11:33.260 --> 11:36.229
You were having stomach
problems, like...

11:36.263 --> 11:38.198
Like sharp pains?

11:41.234 --> 11:43.303
Lisbeth?

11:43.336 --> 11:46.306
Would you like some tea?

11:46.339 --> 11:50.077
It's Momordica charantia.
It purifies the blood.

11:51.244 --> 11:53.747
You already have some.

11:53.781 --> 11:55.491
Well, you were telling me
that you were having

11:55.515 --> 11:58.919
eating problems, and I've been
having these sharp pains...

11:58.952 --> 12:02.489
I have to be very careful
about who I interact with.

12:02.522 --> 12:06.794
The world is extremely toxic.

12:09.329 --> 12:10.998
But that can't be you...

12:11.031 --> 12:12.499
You...

12:16.536 --> 12:18.839
Kyle loves you, doesn't he?

12:22.075 --> 12:24.211
Yeah.

12:33.086 --> 12:34.387
I'm just messing around

12:34.421 --> 12:37.024
The cake is Godzilla
attacking the city.

12:37.057 --> 12:39.059
Aha, right, yes.

12:39.092 --> 12:40.894
Sexy now.

12:40.928 --> 12:44.031
Right, you're a vampire,
biting the tip.

12:46.199 --> 12:48.235
Yes, thank you. Awesome.

12:48.268 --> 12:49.402
Thank you.

12:49.436 --> 12:52.005
Let's set up for the next bit.

12:52.039 --> 12:53.340
Hey I'm Kyle.

12:53.373 --> 12:56.076
Hey, I'm Megan.
I think we have the same agent.

12:56.109 --> 12:57.987
Maybe that's why we keep
bumping into each other.

12:58.011 --> 12:59.246
What're you doing later?

12:59.279 --> 13:00.924
Just being honored
at some Hollywood party

13:00.948 --> 13:02.282
where Xavier Hughes
is performing.

13:02.315 --> 13:04.484
You know, the youshe.
Ooh, I like parties.

13:04.517 --> 13:06.019
I like you.

13:06.053 --> 13:07.063
Did you wanna talk
about schedule?

13:07.087 --> 13:08.521
- Yes.
- Not really.

13:08.555 --> 13:10.357
The coffee with the
Twitter people tomorrow...

13:10.390 --> 13:12.101
Do you think we could
push them to today after 3:00?

13:12.125 --> 13:14.103
I would love to talk to them
before the gala tonight.

13:14.127 --> 13:15.471
The agency has you
at the gift suite at 3:00.

13:15.495 --> 13:17.297
I thought that was after lunch.

13:17.330 --> 13:20.167
It was, but Stacy
at Balenciaga has strep throat,

13:20.200 --> 13:21.444
so the styling
got pushed to 1:00.

13:21.468 --> 13:23.170
So when are we doing
the phone call?

13:23.203 --> 13:24.447
Can you do it
in the car on the way?

13:24.471 --> 13:26.039
Well, it's not
gonna be great for you.

13:26.073 --> 13:27.283
No, it's fine,
I could listen to music

13:27.307 --> 13:28.351
while I prep for
the Seacrest thing.

13:28.375 --> 13:29.943
There you go.

13:29.977 --> 13:32.012
Hey, Kyle, can I steal you
for a second?

13:32.045 --> 13:34.247
Yeah. I'll be back.

13:34.281 --> 13:36.149
See if Twitter can do a call.

13:36.183 --> 13:37.150
Maybe on the way
to your reads later?

13:37.184 --> 13:38.385
Thank you.

13:38.418 --> 13:40.120
- They're bluffing.
- I doubt it.

13:40.153 --> 13:41.464
Look, you took yourself
out of the movie.

13:41.488 --> 13:42.999
You won't cast somebody
that they like.

13:43.023 --> 13:44.267
I'd pull my money too
if I were them.

13:44.291 --> 13:45.534
Okay, let's just say
they back out.

13:45.558 --> 13:47.070
How much of my own money
do I have to put up?

13:47.094 --> 13:48.061
We are not having
that conversation.

13:48.095 --> 13:49.462
It's just a question.

13:49.496 --> 13:51.207
If you use your money,
you have nobody to answer to.

13:51.231 --> 13:53.100
I love you, but I am
not letting you direct

13:53.133 --> 13:54.501
your first
feature film unchecked.

13:54.534 --> 13:57.304
I'm sorry,
but if we lose Jason and Vic,

13:57.337 --> 13:58.405
we are shutting down.

13:58.438 --> 14:01.041
Look, we have to cast somebody.

14:01.074 --> 14:03.443
I think it
should be Logan Travers.

14:04.477 --> 14:07.180
Ooh, is that
the next cover of "Esquire"?

14:07.214 --> 14:10.283
- "Vanity Fair."
- Oops... still, wow.

14:10.317 --> 14:11.584
I know, I know.

14:11.618 --> 14:14.154
Creative Partners does not play.

14:14.187 --> 14:15.431
I've been with them
for two months,

14:15.455 --> 14:17.257
and they have me,
like, everywhere.

14:17.290 --> 14:21.461
So how are you feeling
about the wedding?

14:21.494 --> 14:23.230
It is hard to say.

14:23.263 --> 14:25.265
Until Terence is
out of the picture,

14:25.298 --> 14:26.499
everything is just temporary.

14:26.533 --> 14:28.235
Yeah.

14:28.268 --> 14:31.204
I mean, Kyle and I are
definitely having more fun,

14:31.238 --> 14:33.206
but, I don't know,
we've been so busy,

14:33.240 --> 14:37.110
sometimes I forget that I still
don't trust him, you know?

14:37.144 --> 14:39.279
Like, not completely.

14:42.149 --> 14:44.051
Are you still having those?

14:44.084 --> 14:45.418
Occasionally.

14:45.452 --> 14:48.088
Well, what did the doctor say?

14:48.121 --> 14:50.090
You haven't been to the doctor?

14:50.123 --> 14:51.600
It's been two months.
What the hell are you doing?

14:51.624 --> 14:55.195
I'm okay, and I'm doing what
I need to be doing right now.

14:55.228 --> 14:56.463
You're not okay.

14:56.496 --> 14:57.606
You're running yourself
into the ground.

14:57.630 --> 15:00.167
I'm building my brand.

15:00.200 --> 15:01.534
And a career, okay?

15:01.568 --> 15:03.270
When shit goes down
with Terence,

15:03.303 --> 15:06.206
I'm gonna need protection.

15:06.239 --> 15:08.041
What's going on with James?

15:08.075 --> 15:10.410
He's finally back in town.
We're having dinner tonight.

15:10.443 --> 15:12.412
- That's my girl.
- Yeah.

15:13.580 --> 15:15.148
I don't know, it's weird.

15:15.182 --> 15:17.117
Just like fullon playing
someone like this?

15:17.150 --> 15:18.418
I'm not used to lying.

15:18.451 --> 15:21.054
The key is to be
as honest as possible.

15:21.088 --> 15:23.456
You only lie if you
absolutely have to.

15:23.490 --> 15:25.192
Okay.

15:25.225 --> 15:28.128
I'm just messing around

15:28.161 --> 15:31.398
