Let's identify our feelings.

15:42.109 --> 15:45.045
- Terence.
- Sadness.

15:45.078 --> 15:47.280
Distant.

15:47.314 --> 15:50.183
Keep trying.

15:50.217 --> 15:52.085
Loneliness.

15:52.119 --> 15:54.487
Good. Everybody present.

15:56.256 --> 15:58.158
Let's talk.

15:58.191 --> 16:00.593
Misaligned narratives
without pairing.

16:00.627 --> 16:03.363
Misaligned narratives
is the symptom.

16:03.396 --> 16:07.200
The root is an absence
of intimacy.

16:07.234 --> 16:09.369
Let's talk about
the emotional first.

16:09.402 --> 16:11.447
Well, let's talk about
the physical intimacy first,

16:11.471 --> 16:13.273
because that's truly
what's been absent here.

16:13.306 --> 16:14.450
You really just
can't let her lead?

16:14.474 --> 16:16.143
It's okay.

16:16.176 --> 16:17.677
We'll get there,
one way or the other.

16:17.710 --> 16:19.646
You aren't having sex
with each other?

16:19.679 --> 16:21.648
Not since the tie
on the doorknob.

16:21.681 --> 16:23.483
Two months ago,
and not much before that.

16:23.516 --> 16:25.261
Is that supposed to justify
the tie on the door?

16:25.285 --> 16:26.662
I don't understand
this emotional reaction.

16:26.686 --> 16:28.155
I really don't.

16:28.188 --> 16:29.689
We're not polyamorous,
we're open.

16:29.722 --> 16:31.424
Feelings for each other
and nobody else.

16:31.458 --> 16:32.568
I follow the rules,
and you won't have sex with me

16:32.592 --> 16:34.327
because of a tie on the door?

16:34.361 --> 16:37.130
It's not rational.
It was a slap in the face.

16:37.164 --> 16:38.665
- It was a head's up.
- Okay.

16:38.698 --> 16:42.235
Obviously there is an
emotional component to the tie,

16:42.269 --> 16:45.605
but an open relationship can't
work unless you are having sex

16:45.638 --> 16:47.640
with each other regularly.

16:47.674 --> 16:52.379
So what do we need
to get us there?

17:15.502 --> 17:17.569
I already called the cops.

17:17.604 --> 17:19.771
If you run now, you can make it.

17:22.309 --> 17:23.542
Keys.

17:23.576 --> 17:25.212
All right, man.

17:25.244 --> 17:26.555
All right, all right,
take it easy, man.

17:26.579 --> 17:27.780
Take it easy.

17:27.814 --> 17:31.284
- Give me the key.
- Okay, okay.

17:31.318 --> 17:32.685
God damn it. Get it.

17:32.719 --> 17:35.788
- Okay, okay, okay.
- Get the key!

17:35.822 --> 17:39.426
Come on.

17:39.459 --> 17:42.695
I didn't say get up.
Don't get up.

17:42.729 --> 17:45.565
I said, don't look at me!

18:14.861 --> 18:17.530
- Kyle, Kyle!
- Megan, over here.

18:17.564 --> 18:20.700
- Kyle, over here.
- Meg, look over here.

18:25.838 --> 18:27.707
Yeah.

18:31.178 --> 18:32.612
It is a thrill for me.

18:32.645 --> 18:34.281
Megan is such an amazing person,

18:34.314 --> 18:35.824
and I'm just really excited
that I get to watch her

18:35.848 --> 18:37.350
accomplish so many great things.

18:37.384 --> 18:38.894
Speaking of which,
can you tell me a little bit

18:38.918 --> 18:40.587
about your wedding?

18:40.620 --> 18:42.655
Like, when is it,
where, who's invited?

18:42.689 --> 18:45.658
Soon, it's a secret,
and, everybody we love.

18:45.692 --> 18:47.327
Thanks.

18:47.360 --> 18:49.796
Domestic violence and abuse
is obviously a huge issue

18:49.829 --> 18:51.931
all over the world,
but by acting locally,

18:51.964 --> 18:54.301
we can directly impact
the people and the families

18:54.334 --> 18:55.835
who need it most.

18:55.868 --> 18:57.937
- Great, thanks.
- Thank you.

18:57.970 --> 18:59.806
- Good night.
- You were born for this.

18:59.839 --> 19:02.409
Well, I definitely
learned a few things from you.

19:06.646 --> 19:09.349
I love you.

19:13.353 --> 19:15.588
If I may direct your attention
to the fireplace,

19:15.622 --> 19:18.758
you will see your new costar.

19:18.791 --> 19:20.793
Logan Travers.

19:20.827 --> 19:22.729
I invited him.

19:22.762 --> 19:24.597
I sent him a script last week.

19:24.631 --> 19:26.409
I spent 20 minutes talking
to him about his dog;

19:26.433 --> 19:27.800
It's a rescue Mastiff.

19:27.834 --> 19:29.602
Look, he is interested
in the part.

19:29.636 --> 19:31.938
And he's good.
What do you think?

19:31.971 --> 19:33.906
Meh.

19:33.940 --> 19:36.743
Okay, more importantly, Jason
and Vic are interested in him.

19:36.776 --> 19:38.221
What, did you already
negotiate his contract,

19:38.245 --> 19:39.688
as well?
It's called "teeing him up."

19:39.712 --> 19:41.681
Listen, just go talk to him.
Please?

19:41.714 --> 19:43.683
He's expecting you.
It's just a conversation.

19:43.716 --> 19:45.218
If you don't like him,
you can say no.

19:52.392 --> 19:55.362
It's where we met.

19:55.395 --> 19:57.230
Not that long ago, in fact.

19:57.264 --> 19:59.899
My God. That thing for the NRDC?

19:59.932 --> 20:03.002
Yeah, you were
schlepping hors d'oeuvres

20:03.035 --> 20:04.471
and mouthing off
to studio heads.

20:04.504 --> 20:06.339
Now, listen to me.

20:06.373 --> 20:08.475
I knew you were special
when we met.

20:08.508 --> 20:10.843
I knew you were capable
of this and so much more,

20:10.877 --> 20:13.446
but "Technicolor Highway"
is your launch pad.

20:13.480 --> 20:15.248
Without it,
none of this happens.

20:15.282 --> 20:16.816
I'm well aware.

20:16.849 --> 20:19.018
Okay, are you also aware
that the investors

20:19.051 --> 20:20.996
are fed up with Kyle
and wanna pull the financing?

20:21.020 --> 20:23.456
No. He didn't tell me that.

20:23.490 --> 20:24.824
Of course, he didn't.

20:24.857 --> 20:26.034
Look, he might be
in denial about this,

20:26.058 --> 20:27.494
but we are out of time.

20:27.527 --> 20:28.761
If we're gonna make this movie

20:28.795 --> 20:29.838
and keep your arrow pointing up,

20:29.862 --> 20:31.298
Logan Travers has to happen.

20:31.331 --> 20:32.932
Kyle can't say no anymore.

20:32.965 --> 20:35.368
- You want me to talk to him.
- Yes, talk to Kyle.

20:35.402 --> 20:36.936
Talk to Logan.
Whatever it takes.

20:36.969 --> 20:38.771
Megan, this is your movie.

20:38.805 --> 20:40.807
And your everything else.

20:48.848 --> 20:50.417
Whiskey.

20:50.450 --> 20:52.385
Actually, I'm pretty sure
Kyle West is God.

20:52.419 --> 20:53.786
He memorized the whole speech.

20:53.820 --> 20:55.688
I watch it every morning
before I run.

20:55.722 --> 20:58.491
"We wanna realize the greatest
version of ourselves."

20:58.525 --> 21:01.961
"That's how we can accomplish
unimaginable things."

21:01.994 --> 21:03.330
No bullshit, my times are down.

21:04.964 --> 21:07.300
I told you I was gonna need
your help with Kyle tonight.

21:07.334 --> 21:08.868
Out and about.

21:08.901 --> 21:12.004
What else?

21:12.038 --> 21:16.343
I didn't come here to
have a goddamn discussion.

21:21.113 --> 21:23.483
Hooper is seriously,
like, half the dudes

21:23.516 --> 21:25.818
that I grew up
with in Kentucky, man.

21:25.852 --> 21:29.456
You know, tough on the outside,
broken on the inside.

21:29.489 --> 21:31.491
And looking for that someone
to hang onto,

21:31.524 --> 21:32.992
but they don't know how.

21:33.025 --> 21:34.994
You know, nobody ever
gave them the tools.

21:35.027 --> 21:36.396
Yeah, that's definitely Hooper.

21:38.030 --> 21:39.866
Little bit?

21:39.899 --> 21:43.436
Come on, we're in this business
to tell our stories, right?

21:43.470 --> 21:45.338
My story's actually Clyde's.

21:45.372 --> 21:46.915
The hot girl
who kills herself at the end.

21:46.939 --> 21:49.376
Yeah.

21:52.111 --> 21:55.047
Wow, okay.

21:55.081 --> 21:56.949
That's deep.

21:56.983 --> 21:59.819
This is a lot of talent
to process at one time.

21:59.852 --> 22:01.354
That's exactly how I just felt.

22:01.388 --> 22:02.531
I don't know how you live
with this guy.

22:02.555 --> 22:05.024
Aw, he makes it easy, trust me.

22:05.057 --> 22:06.859
Megan Morrison,
meet Logan Travers.

22:06.893 --> 22:08.561
Kyle and I caught "Park Circle"

22:08.595 --> 22:10.072
at the Venice
Film Festival last year,

22:10.096 --> 22:11.398
and we just loved it.

22:11.431 --> 22:13.500
So nice of you to say.

22:16.869 --> 22:18.838
Chardonnay, please.

22:30.517 --> 22:33.786
- Logan Travers.
- Nasim.

22:33.820 --> 22:35.154
What're you doing here?

22:35.187 --> 22:37.424
I'll be honest,
I'm straight up using you

22:37.457 --> 22:38.991
so I can meet these two.

22:39.025 --> 22:41.528
Congratulations.
This is so exciting.

22:41.561 --> 22:42.995
And I love your charity.

22:43.029 --> 22:44.464
Thank you.

22:44.497 --> 22:45.965
Kyle and Megan,
meet Nasim Anand.

22:45.998 --> 22:47.500
This is my old partner in crime.

22:47.534 --> 22:50.002
We did a horrible
movie together.

22:50.036 --> 22:52.572
But I just have to say,
I am totally obsessed

22:52.605 --> 22:54.507
with the Institute
of the Higher Mind right now.

22:54.541 --> 22:56.042
That sounds unhealthy.

22:56.075 --> 22:57.444
Yeah, my boyfriend

22:57.477 --> 22:59.011
says the same thing.

22:59.045 --> 23:00.589
But, you know, the speech
you gave in that video

23:00.613 --> 23:01.881
was amazing.

23:01.914 --> 23:03.950
You're really inspirational.

23:05.685 --> 23:08.455
There he is.

23:08.488 --> 23:10.557
You know, I discovered this one.

23:10.590 --> 23:12.425
I discovered you.

23:12.459 --> 23:14.427
You were very small,

23:14.461 --> 23:16.829
but I thought to myself,
he's gonna be great.

23:19.466 --> 23:22.869
That's right. Yes,
this man showed me the way.

23:22.902 --> 23:24.571
Come on, let me buy you a drink.

23:24.604 --> 23:25.972
Let's go. Excuse us.

23:32.512 --> 23:34.113
I almost died.

23:34.146 --> 23:35.691
Yeah, well, tomorrow
you're gonna wish you died.

23:35.715 --> 23:37.584
Look, let's get you
some coffee, all right?

23:37.617 --> 23:39.118
To have him here tonight,

23:39.151 --> 23:44.591
so please welcome
the incredible Xavier Hughes!

23:51.531 --> 23:55.234
That's my boyfriend.

24:05.545 --> 24:07.547
Yeah.

24:07.580 --> 24:09.148
Xavier Hughes
playing at an event

24:09.181 --> 24:10.983
where you're being honored.

24:11.017 --> 24:14.020
His first album... best
breakup therapy in the world.

24:14.053 --> 24:16.523
My God, "Buried Under
a Blanket and Barely Alive".

24:17.657 --> 24:18.958
What do you think, Mr. Travers,

24:18.991 --> 24:20.268
are we gonna do
this movie together?

24:20.292 --> 24:22.161
Shoot, I hope so.

24:22.194 --> 24:24.664
It's kind of up to El Jefe
at this point, though.

24:24.697 --> 24:26.633
He's a little hard to read?

24:26.666 --> 24:29.669
Kyle loves you. Believe me.

24:29.702 --> 24:33.072
Well, you are
extremely believable.

24:33.105 --> 24:34.607
Just propped your
drunk husband up

24:34.641 --> 24:36.543
with a triple cappuccino.

24:36.576 --> 24:37.753
What the hell is wrong with him?

24:37.777 --> 24:39.546
I have no idea,

24:39.579 --> 24:41.123
but they look cute together,
don't they?

24:41.147 --> 24:43.916
What do you think?

24:43.950 --> 24:45.585
Megan, Logan.

24:45.618 --> 24:46.929
Can Friendspace Live
just grab a moment

24:46.953 --> 24:48.054
before the ceremony begins?

24:48.087 --> 24:49.756
- Yeah, of course!
- Okay.

24:53.760 --> 24:55.528
We are streaming live here

24:55.562 --> 24:57.129
from the Rising Women
of Hollywood Gala

24:57.163 --> 24:59.666
with Megan Morrison
and Logan Travers.

24:59.699 --> 25:01.033
- Hi, you guys.
- Hi, Friendspace.

25:01.067 --> 25:02.602
Hi, there.

25:02.635 --> 25:04.547
Now, are you guys talking
business or are you just

25:04.571 --> 25:07.139
appreciating how incredible
Xavier Hughes is?

25:07.173 --> 25:09.008
Well, a little bit of both.

25:09.041 --> 25:11.678
Megan, you have
a huge movie coming up,

25:11.711 --> 25:13.121
and you're about to marry
one of the biggest stars

25:13.145 --> 25:15.014
in the entire world.

25:15.047 --> 25:16.967
Talk to us a little bit
about how working with...

25:18.017 --> 25:21.988
Megan?

25:24.090 --> 25:25.692
Megan, Megan.

25:25.725 --> 25:27.960
Hey, Megan, Megan. Hey, Megan.

25:27.994 --> 25:30.229
Hey, sweetie.

25:30.262 --> 25:31.764
Not right now.

25:36.202 --> 25:37.946
Three hours since Megan
Morrison's collapse

25:37.970 --> 25:39.848
at the Alist Hollywood event
and we already have

25:39.872 --> 25:41.808
conflicting insider reports
of drugs, pregnancy,

25:41.841 --> 25:44.644
and an eating disorder.

25:44.677 --> 25:47.279
1.8 million live views.

25:47.313 --> 25:49.716
The agency keeps
pestering me for answers.

25:49.749 --> 25:51.851
Because the new client
launch fell apart?

25:51.884 --> 25:53.119
Screw 'em.

25:53.152 --> 25:54.621
This insider's going with drugs.

25:54.654 --> 25:55.831
No, it's not drugs, all right?

25:55.855 --> 25:57.724
I would know.

25:57.757 --> 25:59.768
Yeah, that's the problem...
You think you know everything,

25:59.792 --> 26:02.261
until you realize
you don't know anything.

26:03.896 --> 26:05.765
And this is Jason and Vic
for the third time.

26:05.798 --> 26:07.634
We need to talk about Logan.

26:07.667 --> 26:08.968
Not now we don't.

26:09.001 --> 26:11.337
Kyle, this fiasco
just makes things worse.

26:11.370 --> 26:14.206
Please, just let me give them
something to stop the carnage.

26:15.775 --> 26:17.810
How is she?

26:17.844 --> 26:19.879
She'll be okay here
for the night.

26:19.912 --> 26:21.914
This is for the pain.

26:21.948 --> 26:23.382
If you can convince her
to take it.

26:23.415 --> 26:24.855
She wouldn't accept
anything from me.

26:26.285 --> 26:27.386
I took some blood.

26:27.419 --> 26:28.888
I'll run it over the zombies

26:28.921 --> 26:31.290
at the lab
and be back in the morning.

26:31.323 --> 26:34.894
She doesn't wanna admit it, but
she's wound up like a spring.

26:34.927 --> 26:38.330
Whatever you could do to keep
her relaxed would be good.

26:38.364 --> 26:42.001
Good night.

26:53.746 --> 26:55.347
It's okay.

27:34.921 --> 27:36.455
Yoohoo.

27:36.488 --> 27:37.957
You're very focused.

27:37.990 --> 27:39.926
You having a hard time deciding?

27:39.959 --> 27:41.360
Um...

27:41.393 --> 27:42.729
There's no rush.

27:42.762 --> 27:45.765
You can just talk to me instead.

27:45.798 --> 27:47.967
I'm sorry, um...

27:48.000 --> 27:49.936
I'm... I'm excited to see you.

27:49.969 --> 27:53.272
It's just, I feel like
we've kind of skipped over...

27:53.305 --> 27:55.307
something.

27:57.009 --> 27:59.746
The explanation for why
you ghosted me at work.

27:59.779 --> 28:03.983
For weeks, and then
how we got here from there.

28:04.016 --> 28:05.752
I'm sorry.

28:05.785 --> 28:08.387
Your feelings are
completely valid.

28:08.420 --> 28:12.825
But... but shouldn't we just
focus on moving forward?

28:14.060 --> 28:16.062
We should, we should.

28:16.095 --> 28:18.330
I... I give that advice every day.

28:18.364 --> 28:21.734
- But...
- Look.

28:21.768 --> 28:24.403
This is the first job I've had

28:24.436 --> 28:26.906
where I don't feel like
I'm settling

28:26.939 --> 28:28.975
in any way.

28:29.008 --> 28:30.943
And I'm scared.

28:30.977 --> 28:36.482
I got scared of a personal
relationship ruining that.

28:36.515 --> 28:39.118
That's all.

28:39.151 --> 28:41.287
And I didn't handle it well.

28:41.320 --> 28:44.123
Well, if you're scared,
then... then...

28:44.156 --> 28:45.892
No.

28:48.060 --> 28:50.863
I'm settled in now.

28:50.897 --> 28:54.066
And I think there's room
for both.

28:57.436 --> 28:59.906
Ordinary stress can really
cause that kind of pain?

28:59.939 --> 29:02.775
There's nothing ordinary
about her narrative right now.

29:02.809 --> 29:05.377
You need to find ways
to manage the pressure.

29:05.411 --> 29:07.880
You might start by taking
something off your plate.

29:12.184 --> 29:13.820
He's talking about the movie.

29:13.853 --> 29:15.463
He's gonna tell them
that I'm not up for it.

29:15.487 --> 29:16.956
- God damn it.
- Relax.

29:16.989 --> 29:17.990
You're jumping the gun.

29:18.024 --> 29:19.926
He's IHM, Shaun.

29:19.959 --> 29:21.060
Don't tell me I'm wrong

29:21.093 --> 29:22.533
for thinking
bad things might happen.

29:22.561 --> 29:26.065
It's not gonna help.

29:26.098 --> 29:28.467
You need to chill, Megan.

29:28.500 --> 29:30.145
If you don't wanna
believe the doctor, fine,

29:30.169 --> 29:31.503
but believe your body.

29:31.537 --> 29:33.072
It's telling you the same thing.

29:33.105 --> 29:34.817
All right, maybe I'm just
getting stomach cancer,

29:34.841 --> 29:36.375
like my mom had.

29:36.408 --> 29:38.945
You need to stop spinning out.

29:38.978 --> 29:40.880
Okay?

29:42.148 --> 29:43.883
I actually have some potential

29:43.916 --> 29:45.952
good news.

29:45.985 --> 29:50.156
I think I can convince James
to take me to the Facility.

29:51.891 --> 29:53.960
He's going back up tomorrow.

29:53.993 --> 29:57.363
Hopefully I'll learn something
that can actually help us out.

29:57.396 --> 29:59.999
And take something
off your plate.

30:00.032 --> 30:01.509
Because he's not right
for the part!

30:01.533 --> 30:03.035
How many times
do I have to say it?

30:03.069 --> 30:04.837
No one's gonna force Logan
down my throat.

30:04.871 --> 30:06.372
Not Jason and Vic, and not you.

30:06.405 --> 30:08.140
I will kill
this movie completely.

30:08.174 --> 30:10.042
That is exactly
what you've been doing

30:10.076 --> 30:11.143
for the past two months.

30:12.879 --> 30:14.122
Jason and Vic want an answer
on Logan Travers

30:14.146 --> 30:15.514
and apparently
that answer is "no."

30:15.547 --> 30:17.016
Why?

30:17.049 --> 30:19.986
I don't wanna
listen to this anymore.

30:20.019 --> 30:22.021
I have worked my ass off
on this movie.

30:22.054 --> 30:23.155
And so has she.

30:23.189 --> 30:24.623
But none of that's gonna matter

30:24.656 --> 30:27.126
because you let your shit
get in the way.

30:41.941 --> 30:45.011
Don't look at me!

30:45.044 --> 30:48.948
I said don't look at me!

31:09.635 --> 31:12.338
When DeAnn said you let
your shit get in the way,

31:12.371 --> 31:15.107
what'd she mean?

31:15.141 --> 31:16.581
She thinks
I'm jealous about Logan.

31:16.608 --> 31:20.312
Or anybody else up for the part.

31:20.346 --> 31:23.015
Sounds a little simplistic.

31:23.049 --> 31:26.318
Yeah, except for when I met
Lisbeth on set, I was single,

31:26.352 --> 31:28.454
and she was dating the director.

31:28.487 --> 31:30.356
Lisbeth.

31:30.389 --> 31:32.024
Yeah.

31:32.058 --> 31:35.427
It got really dramatic.

31:35.461 --> 31:38.230
And we all got caught up in it.

31:38.264 --> 31:40.008
And you're afraid the same
thing's gonna happen

31:40.032 --> 31:42.034
with me and Logan?

31:42.068 --> 31:43.402
That's DeAnn's theory, yeah.

31:43.435 --> 31:46.105
I'm asking you.

31:47.439 --> 31:50.176
Right, "me" as in me.

31:55.047 --> 31:56.524
You know, I've been pretending
to be other people

31:56.548 --> 32:00.219
for a long time,

32:00.252 --> 32:03.155
but when I direct,

32:03.189 --> 32:06.625
I'm not gonna be able to hide
behind an image anymore.

32:06.658 --> 32:09.428
The way I think,
the way I see the world...

32:12.198 --> 32:16.168
It's all gonna be exposed.

32:16.202 --> 32:20.339
And the movie doesn't
have to be perfect.

32:20.372 --> 32:23.575
You know, nobody's perfect.

32:23.609 --> 32:26.245
But it has to be right.

32:26.278 --> 32:29.515
Why would I settle
for anything less?

32:29.548 --> 32:31.217
You can't.

32:31.250 --> 32:32.551
You know, Logan's really good.

32:32.584 --> 32:34.286
I mean, the guy's talented.

32:34.320 --> 32:37.389
You know, why... why wouldn't
I pull the trigger?

32:41.660 --> 32:44.063
Maybe DeAnn's right.

32:44.096 --> 32:45.331
Maybe I am jealous.

32:48.334 --> 32:49.535
You know...

32:52.371 --> 32:54.340
We have a contract

32:54.373 --> 32:57.076
that forbids me from having
an affair with a costar,

32:57.109 --> 32:58.244
or anyone else.

32:58.277 --> 32:59.411
Yes, I do know that.

32:59.445 --> 33:00.612
Come on, please.

33:00.646 --> 33:02.214
Contracts get broken
all the time.

33:02.248 --> 33:05.151
Yeah,
maybe by major movie stars.

33:05.184 --> 33:07.553
Last year, I was a waitress.

33:07.586 --> 33:10.356
I'm not throwing away
$10 million on a piece of ass.

33:10.389 --> 33:11.599
You're probably the first
person in Hollywood

33:11.623 --> 33:15.661
ever to say that.

33:24.770 --> 33:29.408
You know, that was really
beautiful, what you said.

33:29.441 --> 33:31.577
About the movie being an
expression of who you are

33:31.610 --> 33:32.644
on the inside.

33:32.678 --> 33:34.346
And you're right,

33:34.380 --> 33:38.317
it's something that people
haven't seen before,

33:38.350 --> 33:40.652
but you showed it to me.

33:40.686 --> 33:43.189
And I loved it.

33:43.222 --> 33:46.258
And look, I know things
have been crazy,

33:46.292 --> 33:48.627
but I feel like
we're growing closer.

33:51.230 --> 33:53.632
That feels really good.

33:53.665 --> 33:56.602
And I won't let anyone... anyone...

33:56.635 --> 33:59.705
Get in the way of that.

33:59.738 --> 34:01.707
Me neither.

34:03.342 --> 34:05.411
Okay.

34:05.444 --> 34:07.346
So...

34:07.379 --> 34:10.716
knowing that, how do you really
feel about Logan Travers?

34:18.324 --> 34:21.226
Well, guess
who's in the neighborhood.

34:25.764 --> 34:29.534
I swear,
Berglund just invades me.

34:29.568 --> 34:31.703
You have amazing taste.

34:31.737 --> 34:33.772
I'm gonna go to bed
in a few minutes.

34:35.341 --> 34:38.244
I mean, she's totally nice, just

34:38.277 --> 34:39.710
a bit much right now.

34:39.745 --> 34:42.313
Yeah, we'll keep it short.

34:42.348 --> 34:44.550
Well, we're so glad
that you're all right.

34:44.583 --> 34:47.253
I hope it's okay that
we invited ourselves over.

34:47.286 --> 34:49.420
No, no, it's very sweet.

34:49.455 --> 34:53.458
And bringing chocolate
makes everything okay, so...

34:53.492 --> 34:56.228
You know, I have this very
strong feeling about you guys.

34:56.262 --> 34:58.397
Like, we're supposed
to be friends, you know?

34:58.430 --> 35:00.566
- Something in your gut.
- Yeah, exactly.

35:00.599 --> 35:02.634
I mean, we kind of match,
don't we?

35:02.668 --> 35:04.603
You and Xavier
are both big stars.

35:04.636 --> 35:06.605
Megan and I are
both on the rise.

35:06.638 --> 35:09.208
Baby, it's not just about
where we're all at with work.

35:09.241 --> 35:10.609
You're right.

35:10.642 --> 35:12.620
I'm just waiting to find out
if they're gonna make me

35:12.644 --> 35:14.280
a series regular, so...

35:14.313 --> 35:15.447
Stressful.

35:15.481 --> 35:17.216
No, no, it's not.

35:17.249 --> 35:19.718
It's... it's all a blessing,
and I am just gonna let it go.

35:21.653 --> 35:25.424
So I have been told
that you have a Lavoie.

35:25.457 --> 35:26.701
Actually, to be honest,
I read about it.

35:26.725 --> 35:28.360
It's upstairs.

35:28.394 --> 35:29.495
You wanna see it?

35:29.528 --> 35:32.564
God, yes.

35:32.598 --> 35:37.503
- I'll... I'll wait here.
- Okay.

35:40.772 --> 35:43.609
We'll go in a minute.
I know you must be exhausted.

35:43.642 --> 35:45.644
It's okay.

35:45.677 --> 35:49.648
You know, before I humiliated
myself last night,

35:49.681 --> 35:51.717
I really enjoyed your set.

35:51.750 --> 35:53.885
I really am a very big fan.

35:53.919 --> 35:55.621
Thank you.

35:55.654 --> 35:57.523
You didn't humiliate yourself.

35:57.556 --> 35:59.491
And you didn't just lie
to make me feel better.

36:08.367 --> 36:10.669
Not me. Kyle.

36:10.702 --> 36:12.271
Hey, you think he'd mind?

36:12.304 --> 36:13.805
Not at all.

36:13.839 --> 36:15.750
I would've offered, I just
thought you might get tired

36:15.774 --> 36:17.409
of people asking you to play.

36:17.443 --> 36:19.311
Nope, I'ma get worried

36:19.345 --> 36:21.513
if people stop
asking me to play.

36:26.352 --> 36:28.820
It's a very interesting choice.

36:30.789 --> 36:35.727
To put a piece with such
strong energy here.

36:35.761 --> 36:37.729
In the bedroom.

36:37.763 --> 36:42.434
I never really thought
about it being anywhere else.

36:42.468 --> 36:44.803
I'm sure it's exactly
where it's supposed to be.

36:58.350 --> 37:00.619
So is this talent
of yours godgiven,

37:00.652 --> 37:01.853
or did you go to Juilliard?

37:01.887 --> 37:05.491
No, no Juilliard.

37:05.524 --> 37:07.559
My mom taught me to play.

37:07.593 --> 37:09.695
She must be amazing.

37:09.728 --> 37:11.630
Yeah, she was.

37:19.505 --> 37:20.639
Sweet 16.

37:21.940 --> 37:25.411
I was 19 when I lost my mom.

37:27.913 --> 37:31.417
We were far too young

37:31.450 --> 37:34.886
To suddenly be so old

37:45.697 --> 37:49.368
Whenever I was sick,
or feeling bad,

37:49.401 --> 37:53.772
I put my ear on the piano
where Mom played and sang,

37:53.805 --> 37:56.442
I'd feel the strings vibrating.

37:56.475 --> 37:59.478
The click of the pedal.

37:59.511 --> 38:02.514
Her voice.

38:02.548 --> 38:05.784
I could feel all of it.

38:05.817 --> 38:08.787
Always made me feel better.

38:15.727 --> 38:18.864
Hey.

38:24.970 --> 38:27.573
Have you ever acted before?

38:36.147 --> 38:40.419
All right, let's go.

38:40.452 --> 38:41.787
Can I DJ?

38:41.820 --> 38:43.389
Sure.

38:43.422 --> 38:46.692
- Sweet.
- Um... first...

38:46.725 --> 38:49.661
Um...

38:49.695 --> 38:51.730
I have to give you this.

38:53.432 --> 38:56.668
It's a blindfold.

38:56.702 --> 38:59.371
I... I can take you
to the Facility,

38:59.405 --> 39:01.507
but I can't let you know
where it is.

39:03.742 --> 39:06.945
Of course, I do. It's just...

39:06.978 --> 39:10.081
You're not authorized.

39:10.115 --> 39:11.817
I'm the inhouse counsel.

39:11.850 --> 39:13.127
I'm sure Terence
wouldn't mind me

39:13.151 --> 39:15.153
knowing where
the Facility is, right?

39:15.186 --> 39:17.723
You're not authorized.

39:21.092 --> 39:24.530
Do you, um, still wanna go?

39:24.563 --> 39:27.899
Yeah! Let's go.

39:27.933 --> 39:29.067
Take me away, captain.

39:46.485 --> 39:49.455
Hey. Do you need to shower?

39:49.488 --> 39:50.856
Eventually.

39:50.889 --> 39:54.192
But I can wait till after lunch.

40:30.996 --> 40:33.765
It's a free country,
for people like you anyway.

40:35.534 --> 40:37.178
People who can pretend
they don't have problems.

40:37.202 --> 40:38.904
You don't know anything about...

40:38.937 --> 40:40.772
Those aren't the lines.
He's improvising.

40:40.806 --> 40:43.542
He's a jazz musician.
Kyle'll work with him.

40:43.575 --> 40:45.152
Well, I don't need to talk
to a therapist or a thief

40:45.176 --> 40:46.812
about my shit.

40:46.845 --> 40:48.089
He's got something
undeniable, though.

40:48.113 --> 40:49.948
And a whole lot
of buzz right now.

40:49.981 --> 40:51.817
It's actually kind of genius.

40:53.652 --> 40:55.153
Well, Kyle's happy.

40:55.186 --> 40:58.924
Jason and Vic are happy.
So yeah, I'm happy.

40:58.957 --> 41:01.259
Good, we'll have
a productive session then.

41:01.292 --> 41:06.164
I cancelled with Bella.

41:06.197 --> 41:08.233
Yeah.

41:08.266 --> 41:10.035
I have a backlog
of work right now,

41:10.068 --> 41:11.870
and honestly,
I don't think we need it.

41:11.903 --> 41:15.607
Okay, did we have sex at some
point that I'm not aware of?

41:17.242 --> 41:20.546
We'll get there. I promise.

41:20.579 --> 41:23.248
Look, for me, it's just
the stress of this movie

41:23.281 --> 41:25.216
more than anything else.

41:25.250 --> 41:29.521
But things are headed
in the right direction again.

41:34.192 --> 41:35.827
It's not the sex
that he's missing.

41:35.861 --> 41:37.162
It's having things his way.

41:37.195 --> 41:39.831
Control.

41:39.865 --> 41:43.068
Personally, I'd miss the sex.

41:43.101 --> 41:44.536
What? It's just easier.

41:44.570 --> 41:47.973
Why make things complicated?

41:48.006 --> 41:49.975
You make everything easier.

42:01.019 --> 42:02.554
I said don't look at me!

42:27.746 --> 42:31.016
Look who's back from the dead.

42:31.049 --> 42:32.293
Did you come to tell me
what a brilliant idea

42:32.317 --> 42:33.885
Xavier Hughes is?

42:33.919 --> 42:37.022
No, actually,
I came to talk to Megan.

42:37.055 --> 42:39.157
About what happened to you.

42:39.190 --> 42:40.626
It's not just stress.

42:40.659 --> 42:43.128
Not when your
entire body shuts down.

42:43.161 --> 42:45.263
Something else is going on.
Something destructive.

42:45.296 --> 42:46.965
And I think you
and I should work together

42:46.998 --> 42:49.167
until we figure out what it is.

42:49.200 --> 42:50.745
Terence, we start
rehearsals tomorrow.

42:50.769 --> 42:52.303
Kyle, it's okay.

42:54.973 --> 42:56.708
I think it's a great idea.

